<para id="RM000000W95011X" category="C" type-id="302I7" name-id="ES0E0-19" from="200601">
<dtccode>P0604</dtccode>
<dtcname>Internal Control Module Random Access Memory (RAM) Error</dtcname>
<dtccode>P0606</dtccode>
<dtcname>ECM / PCM Processor</dtcname>
<dtccode>P0607</dtccode>
<dtcname>Control Module Performance</dtcname>
<dtccode>P0657</dtccode>
<dtcname>Actuator Supply Voltage Circuit / Open</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000W95011X_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00002QA00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The ECM continuously monitors its internal memory status, internal circuits, and output signals sent to the throttle actuator. This self-check ensures that the ECM is functioning properly. If any malfunction is detected, the ECM will set the appropriate DTC and illuminate the MIL.</ptxt>
<ptxt>The ECM memory status is diagnosed by internal "mirroring" of the main CPU and the sub CPU to detect Random Access Memory (RAM) errors. The 2 CPUs also perform continuous mutual monitoring. The ECM illuminates the MIL and sets a DTC if: 1) outputs from the 2 CPUs are different and deviate from the standards, 2) the signals sent to the throttle actuator deviate from the standards, 3) a malfunction is found in the throttle actuator supply voltage, and 4) any other ECM malfunction is found.</ptxt>
